# {{projectName}}

Android-first Lynx application created with Jilatax.

## Development (QR)

```bash
bun i
bun run dev
```

The Android command starts Rspeedy, builds and installs the debug APK, verifies
the ADB reverse tunnel, and launches the app once. The generated APK is located
at `android/app/build/outputs/apk/debug/app-debug.apk`.

To run only the Lynx development APK (Real Mobile):

```bash
bun run run:android
```

When the build is ready, scan the printed QR code with the Lynx application on
the same network to preview the bundle on a device.

## Android App Bundle

```bash
bun run create:aab
```

Configure `android/keystore.properties` from the included example before a
Play Store release. Never commit signing credentials.

Application metadata lives in `app.json`. Android is the only supported native
platform in this phase. The app follows the device light or dark theme and
refreshes automatically when that setting changes.

Default launcher and splash artwork lives in `public/assets/`. Additional local
fonts can be stored in `public/fonts/`; the included JilataX font is applied to
the centered screen text. Update the image paths, background colors, or splash
width in `app.json`; Jilatax synchronizes those resources before each Android
build.

SVG icons can be imported directly as typed ReactLynx components. The generated
settings controls include examples in `src/assets/icons/`; editing one while
`bun run run:android` is active triggers an incremental Rspeedy rebuild and the
normal Jilatax live-reload flow.
